PROBLEM

In a structural laboratory one of the students has found the structure of a PROBLEM protein, modelled by a previous post-doc.  
However, it seems it is incomplete.  According to the experimental data,  this protein works forms a homodimer complex.
But it's unclear the function and if it works at all.

Try to answer the following questions:

a) What function do you think it may have? 
b) Does it belongs to some family of PFAM?. If so, obtain the HMM profile from PFAM and name it p37b.hmm
c) Does the structure of this protein belongs to some fold in SCOP?, which one?
d) Obtain the secondary structure of the problem with DSSP and name it p37e.dssp (WARNING NOTE: DSSP requieres the full MAINCHAIN, 
   with only CA trace it will not work).
e) Do you think the prediction of secondary structure agrees with the actual secondary structure from DSSP?. Obtain an alignment as proof and 
   name it p37f.aln. Is this prediction reliable?
f) Do you think the structure is correct? Can you prove it? show an image of the energies that prove it and name it p37f.png
g) Find if there is some structural problem and show the location of all those you find with an image (name it p37g.png). 
   What's(are) the sequence fragment(s) with this problem?
h) Do you think the protein PROBLEM, as it is originally in the file, can work as a dimer? show an image that can prove it (name it p37i.png)
i) Even if it was a monomer, do you think it will work with the function you selected in answer "a"? Use a sequence alignment (ie. you can reuse
   p37d.aln) to show the conservation/non-conservation of functional residues. 
   Mark the functionally important amino-acids (conserved or non-conserved) in the alignment with the symbol # at the bottom.
j) To further proof your answer in "i": Show an image of the structure of the "active site"/"interface" with the relevant aminoacids that preserve 
   (or don't preserve) the function in its active form 
   (i.e. if it requires another molecule, such as a cofactor like ATP, Ca+2,  etc. or DNA/RNA include it interacting with the corresponding residues of the PROBLEM). 
   Name it p37j.png
k) If the structure of the PROBLEM was incorrect (answer in g), try to fix it. 
   Name the new monomer model as p37k.pdb. Compare the energies with PROSA (show the result with an image and name it p37k.png)
l) Do you think your new model can work as a dimer? If so, obtain the structure of the dimer and name it p28l.pdb. 
   Show with an image if the original model couldn't make a dimer, why your new model can (or cannot) make it?. Name the image p28l.png
m) Do you think the dimer, once you have fixed the model, will be functional?  Use an image showing the relevant residues that you consider will preserve (or won't)
   preserve the function.  Name the image p28m.png, name the PDB p28m.pdb

